{"parse":{"title":"Damian Le Bas","pageid":3135575,"revid":846299522,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">This article is about the British artist. It is not to be confused with his son the writer Damian \"Danes\" Le Bas.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Damian Le Bas</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<span style=\"display:none\">(<span class=\"bday\">1963-01-30</span>)</span>January 30, 1963<br /><span class=\"birthplace\"><a href=\"/wiki/Sheffield\" title=\"Sheffield\">Sheffield</a></span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\nDecember 9, 2017<span style=\"display:none\">(2017-12-09)</span> (aged&#160;54)<br /><span class=\"deathplace\"><a href=\"/wiki/Worthing\" title=\"Worthing\">Worthing</a></span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Nationality</th><td class=\"category\">\nBritish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Occupation</th><td class=\"role\">\nBritish artist</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Damian Le Bas</b> (30 January 1963, <a href=\"/wiki/Sheffield\" title=\"Sheffield\">Sheffield</a> \u2013 9 December 2017, <a href=\"/wiki/Worthing\" title=\"Worthing\">Worthing</a>) was a British artist associated with the <a href=\"/wiki/Outsider_art\" title=\"Outsider art\">Outsider Art</a> (or \"Art Brut\") label, as well a leading exponent of the \"Roma Revolution\" in art. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Collections\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Collections</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Exhibitions\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Exhibitions</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Life\">Life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Damian_Le_Bas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Le Bas was of <a href=\"/wiki/Irish_traveller\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Irish traveller\">Irish Traveller</a> heritage.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Le Bas attended the <a href=\"/wiki/Royal_College_of_Art\" title=\"Royal College of Art\">Royal College of Art</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-SS_Ob_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SS_Ob-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>He lived and worked with his wife, the <a href=\"/wiki/Romani_people\" title=\"Romani people\">Romany</a> artist <a href=\"/wiki/Delaine_Le_Bas\" title=\"Delaine Le Bas\">Delaine Le Bas</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-SS_Ob_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SS_Ob-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> in <a href=\"/wiki/West_Sussex\" title=\"West Sussex\">West Sussex</a> on the south coast. He was the father of writer <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Damian_Le_Bas_(writer)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Damian Le Bas (writer) (page does not exist)\">Damian Le Bas</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Collections\">Collections</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Damian_Le_Bas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Collections\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Since 1987 several of Le Bas' pieces are held in the Musgrave-Kinley Collection of works by key Outsider artists, administered by <a href=\"/wiki/Monika_Kinley\" title=\"Monika Kinley\">Monika Kinley</a>, until her death in 2014.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Guardian_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Guardian-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> His more recent work is found, among others, in the collections of Perpetuum Mobile.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Exhibitions\">Exhibitions</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Damian_Le_Bas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Exhibitions\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>He exhibited frequently in the UK and Germany, and his works have been shown at Moderna Museet in Sweden,<sup id=\"cite_ref-perpetualmobile_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-perpetualmobile-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> in Japan, France, Finland and the United States. He was well-known in Outsider Art circles, and was exhibited as part of a survey-show of <a href=\"/wiki/Art_brut\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Art brut\">Art Brut</a> at Malm\u00f6 Konsthall in 1991.<sup id=\"cite_ref-damianlebasartbrut_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-damianlebasartbrut-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> He was a participant of the <a href=\"/wiki/Prague_Biennale\" title=\"Prague Biennale\">Prague Biennale 3</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-praguebiennale_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-praguebiennale-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In later years, the Traveller - Romani - Gypsy experience became a recurrent theme in his work. Le Bas was invited to participate in the 1st Roma Pavilion at the <a href=\"/wiki/Venice_Biennale\" title=\"Venice Biennale\">Venice Biennale</a> in 2007.<sup id=\"cite_ref-opensocietyfoundations_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-opensocietyfoundations-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> He subsequently became a driving force behind the Perpetual Romani-Gypsy Pavilion in Venice in 2009<sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> and the co-initiator of the 4th Roma Pavilion which took place in Berlin in 2013.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>He exhibited frequently in the UK and Germany, and his works have been shown in Japan, France, Finland, Sweden and in the United States.\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Malm%C3%B6_Konsthall\" title=\"Malm\u00f6 Konsthall\">Malm\u00f6 Konsthall</a>, Malm\u00f6, Scania, Sweden, 1991. A survey-show of <a href=\"/wiki/Art_brut\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Art brut\">Art Brut</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-damianlebasartbrut_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-damianlebasartbrut-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>1st Roma Pavilion at the <a href=\"/wiki/Venice_Biennale\" title=\"Venice Biennale\">Venice Biennale</a>, 2007.<sup id=\"cite_ref-opensocietyfoundations_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-opensocietyfoundations-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Moderna_Museet\" title=\"Moderna Museet\">Moderna Museet</a>, Stockholm, Sweden<sup id=\"cite_ref-perpetualmobile_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-perpetualmobile-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Prague_Biennale\" title=\"Prague Biennale\">Prague Biennale 3</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-praguebiennale_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-praguebiennale-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Damian_Le_Bas&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/high-profile-stories-of-children-expose-europes-anti-roma-prejudice/article15200641/\">\"High-profile stories of children expose Europe's anti-Roma prejudice\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">11 December</span> 2017</span>  &#8211; via The Globe and Mail.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=High-profile+stories+of+children+expose+Europe%E2%80%99s+anti-Roma+prejudice&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theglobeandmail.com%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fhigh-profile-stories-of-children-expose-europes-anti-roma-prejudice%2Farticle15200641%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADamian+Le+Bas\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-SS_Ob-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-SS_Ob_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-SS_Ob_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Steward, Sue (29 October 2000). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/2000/oct/29/life1.